<P>
HENRY K. ELDER, 62; REAL ESTATE EXECUTIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Henry K. Elder, a prominent Westside Los Angeles real estate executive for more 
than 30 years and most recently vice president and general sales manager of 
George Elkins Co. of Beverly Hills, died Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
He was 62 and died of a heart attack at UCLA Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
Born in Los Angeles, he was a graduate of the USC School of Business 
Administration and at one time had been president of the 65-year-old Elkins 
company. He was a past president of both the Beverly Hills and Los Angeles 
boards of realtors. 
</P>
<P>
Survivors include his wife, Virginia, two sons and a daughter who encourage 
donations to a favored charity. 
</P>
