<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOWARD EQUALITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I didn't feel the article "Putting 'X' into Xmas: A More Sensible Approach" was 
representative of myself or most of the other Jewish people I know. It is true 
the December holidays are difficult but it is possible to walk a tightrope of 
emotions between Hanukkah and Christmas. 
</P>
<P>
I appreciate the desire of teachers and merchants to include Jewish children 
and consumers in the holiday spirit, and I don't mind my children being able to 
make different art projects and sing Hanukkah songs along with their Christian 
friends. 
</P>
<P>
Our neighbors are reaching out to us and attempting to include us while 
allowing us to celebrate our own beliefs in schools and communities. I feel 
this is a very positive approach to coexisting and maintaining our special 
heritage. 
</P>
