<TEXT>
<P>
Bonnie Blair won the women's competition at the World Sprint Speed Skating 
Championships at Heerenveen, Netherlands, scoring a record 159.435 points. The 
old mark was 160.060, set by East Germany's Karin Kania three years ago. 
</P>
<P>
Blair, who won the 500 meters on Saturday and Sunday, edged defending champion 
Christa Luding of East Germany, who also bettered the old record with 159.600 
points. 
</P>
<P>
Igor Zhelezovsky of the Soviet Union won three of four events and equaled 
fellow Soviet Pavel Pegov's world record of 1 minute 12.58 seconds in the 1,000 
to set a record of 145.945 points in the men's competition. 
</P>
