</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marc Girardelli became the first person to win all four skiing disciplines in 
the same season when he won the final World Cup men's super-giant slalom at 
Whistler, Canada. 
</P>
<P>
Girardelli, who was born in Austria and skis for Luxembourg, swept down the 
39-gate Whistler Mountain course in British Columbia in 1 minute 39.84 seconds. 
Lars-Boerje Eriksson of Sweden was second and Pirmin Zurbriggen of Switzerland 
was third. 
</P>
<P>
Girardelli, who has clinched the World Cup overall title with four technical 
events remaining in Japan, earlier won three downhills, two giant slaloms and a 
slalom. 
</P>
<P>
The super-giant slalom was added to the World Cup circuit in 1982. 
</P>
</TEXT>
