<TEXT>
<P>
Louisiana State's Dawn Sowell won both the 55-meter and 200-meter dashes at the 
Southeastern Conference indoor track and field championships in Baton Rouge, 
La. 
</P>
<P>
Her time in the 55 was 6.58, which breaks the SEC record of 6.60 set by Gwen 
Torrence of Georgia in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
LSU won both the men's and women's team titles. 
</P>
