<HEADLINE>
<P>
TISH JOHNSON SETS LPBT RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tish Johnson of Panorama City set a Ladies Pro Bowlers Tour nine-game record 
Sunday to take a 121-pin lead over Paula Drake of Broken Arrow, Okla., after 
one round of the $30,000 San Dimas tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson averaged 245, including a 298 game and a three-game series of 804, en 
route to a record total of 2,205 pins, breaking by one pin the LPBT record set 
by Karen Ellingsworth in 1986. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, a 26-year-old left-hander, is trying for her sixth career title. 
Drake, bidding for her first title, finished at 2,084. 
</P>
<P>
Anne Marie Pike of Anaheim, who started the tournament with a 296 game, was 
third at 2,055 followed by Dana Miller-Mackie of Sydney, Australia, at 2,050 
and Dede Davidson of Southgate, Mich., at 2,036. 
</P>
<P>
Aleta Sill of Dearborn, Mich., was sixth at 2,032. 
</P>
</TEXT>
