<HEADLINE>
<P>
SLEW CITY SLEW WINS FEATURE RACE AT GULFSTREAM PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HALLANDALE, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Slew City Slew led every step of the way to win the $300,000 Gulfstream Park 
Handicap Sunday, beating Bold Midway by 1 1/4 lengths. 
</P>
<P>
Cryptoclearance, the odds-on favorite, came from last but never threatened as 
he finished third, 1 1/2 lengths behind Bold Midway. Intensive Command was 
fourth in the field of six going 1 1/4 miles. 
</P>
<P>
Ridden by Angel Cordero Jr., Slew City Slew was timed in 2:03 1/5. He was 
coupled in the betting with Dynaformer and the entry paid $5.20, $3.40 and 
$2.10. Bold Midway paid $6.20 and $2.10. Cryptoclearance returned $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
Slew City Slew opened a two-length lead and increased it to three lengths while 
turning for home. Slew City Slew led by four lengths at the eighth pole and 
held off Bold Midway's charge. 
</P>
<P>
"It was perfect," Cordero said. "Nobody tried to run with us. I was on an easy 
lead and we had plenty left when we turned for home. This is a real tough 
horse, especially when he can set his own pace." 
</P>
<P>
Owned by Joe Allen and the Tayhill Stable, Slew City Slew is a 5-year-old son 
of Seattle Slew. He won six of 18 starts and finished in the money 13 times 
last year, earning $465,150. Sunday he earned $180,000. 
</P>
<P>
In his previous start, he gave way to Cryptoclearance in the late stages of the 
Donn Handicap, finishing second. 
</P>
</TEXT>
