<P>
Frank Sinatra, Liza Minnelli and Sammy Davis Jr.'s concert Saturday in Tokyo 
grossed $1.8 million, the highest ever for a Japan concert in a 7,000-seat 
venue. Ticket prices for the concert at NK Hall were about $520, $320 and $200. 
The concert will air on the Tokyo Broadcasting System on Saturday as a two-hour 
prime-time special. Sinatra, Minnelli and Davis continue their world tour with 
four concerts in Australia and two in Honolulu before returning to Los Angeles 
for a three-week break. They play concert halls in Europe on a five-week tour 
in April and May. Shauna Snow 
