<P>
MILITARY EXERCISES BOOST NOISE AT EL TORO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents near the El Toro Marine Corps Air Station may experience an increase 
in noise, base officials said, because of regional military exercises that 
began Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The additional noise is expected to last through Tuesday morning because of 
extended operating hours for the base, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The airfield will operate from 3 a.m. to 8 p.m. today and until 9 p.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Officials did not disclose the nature of the exercises. 
