<HEADLINE>
<P>
TITANS' JONES REACHES PAC-10 WRESTLING FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Heavyweight David Jones of Cal State Fullerton reached the final of the Pacific 
10 wrestling championships with a 5-2 victory over Tom Osendorf of Cal State 
Bakersfield Sunday at Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
Jones, who is ranked fifth in the nation, will face third-ranked Pat McDade of 
Boise State today in the final of the heavyweight division. They have met twice 
this season in the Las Vegas tournament, with McDade winning both times. 
</P>
<P>
Jones is 31-3 on the season. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton had three other wrestlers advance to today's competition, which will 
decide first through sixth place in each division. 
</P>
<P>
In the 118-pound division, the Titans' Erin Millsap lost to Van Vidlak of 
Oregon, 18-5, in the semifinals. Millsap came back to defeat Anthony Tamez of 
Fresno State, 12-10, to qualify for the third-place match. 
</P>
<P>
At 134, Cody Bryant lost to Glenn Jarrett of Oregon, 3-2, in the semifinals. 
Bryant then defeated Robert Tabarez of Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, 9-2, to 
qualify for the third-place match. At 150, Scott Schumm lost to Thom Ortiz of 
Arizona State, 15-6, in the semifinals. Schumm then defeated Bill Grundler of 
Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, 6-0, to qualify for the third-place match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
