<P>
LUMBER FALLS ON CAR, KILLS DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 59-year-old woman was killed today when her car was crushed by a 
lumber-carrying trailer truck that tipped over, Los Angeles police said. The 
7:39 a.m. accident at Devonshire Street and Topanga Canyon Boulevard in 
Chatsworth closed the intersection for more than two hours. Police identified 
the victim as Ella Gormley of Sepulveda. 
</P>
<P>
Gormley's car was stopped in a westbound lane on Devonshire waiting to turn 
south, officials said. When a tractor truck pulling two trailers of lumber 
north on Topanga Canyon Boulevard turned east on Devonshire the cab and the 
first trailer tipped over. The trailer landed directly on top of Gormley's car, 
killing her. The truck driver, Angelo Bazza, 25, of Petaluma, was not charged 
pending investigation on whether the trailer was overloaded. 
</P>
