<P>
HUNGARY ASKS U.N. ROMANIA PROBE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GENEVA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hungary, in an unprecedented attack by one East Bloc state against another, 
today demanded that the U.N. Commission on Human Rights investigate violations 
of basic freedoms in neighboring Romania. 
</P>
<P>
Gyula Horn, Hungarian state secretary for foreign affairs, delivered the demand 
at the commission's annual meeting. Horn specifically denounced the repression 
of the Hungarian ethnic minority in Romania and a wholesale destruction of 
villages to facilitate a forced industrialization program ordered by Romanian 
leader Nicolae Ceausescu. Budapest backs a Swedish proposal that the U.N. human 
rights body appoint someone to investigate Romania, he said. 
</P>
