<P>
JAILED TRADER FINED $1.125 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A futures trader already serving a six-year jail term for donning a wig and 
disguising himself in the pits was fined a record $1.125 million and barred 
permanently from the Chicago Board of Trade, the exchange said today. 
</P>
<P>
Trader Thompson Sanders must pay the record fine for engaging in a yearlong 
scheme where he and several confederates used counterfeit trading credentials 
and disguises so they could acknowledge only the trades where they turned a 
profit and walk away from losing transactions. 
</P>
